
	Microsoft-WORD:
	===============
		
		use:
			documentation purpose.
		
		documentation:
			- letter
			- book
			- resume
			- newspaper
			- mailmerge
			- label
			- question paper
			- bond					

	how to open microsoft word?
	===========================		
			1) start->programs -->,microsoft office -->microsoft word.
			2) start->run->winword-->ok.

	word parts:
	==========
		 1) title
		 2) menu
		 3) menu items
		 4) Ruler (size)
		 5) Scrollbar(vertical,horizontal)
		 6) layout(typing area)
		 7) status bar	
	
	word shortcut:
	=============
	
	save as : f12
	open: ctrl+o
	new window : ctrl+n
	close window: alt +f4 
	
	left align : ctrl + l
	right align: ctrl + r
	center align: ctrl+e
	justify align: ctrl + j
	
	bold: ctrl + b
	italic: ctrl + i
	underline: ctrl + u
	
	full caps/first caps/all small : shift+f3
	
	font size increase: ctrl+] ( one by one increment)
	font size decrease: ctrl+[
	
			  : ctrl+shift+> (already mentioned size increment)
			    ctrl+shift+<

	line space:
			ctrl+0,1,2,5

	select all: ctrl+a
	
	select particular text: shift+ arrow key

	unselect text: arrow key	

	cut: ctrl+ x or shift+delte
	
	copy: ctrl + c or ctrl + insert

	paste: ctrl + v or shift+ insert


	move cursor first char of each word: ctrl + right/left arrow.


	move cursor each paragraph of first char: ctrl+ up/down arrow.

	move cursor next page: (page break): ctrl + enter 
		use: second page char don't move.

	find: ctrl + f
	
	replace: ctrl+ h

	menu shortcut: f10

	subscript: h2so4 (ctrl + =)
	superscript: a2+b2+2ab (ctrl+ shift+ +)		

		
			
	
	
	
			
